Nancy Tyagi’s rise to fame has been a whirlwind, with a defining moment that solidified her place as a go-getter in the fashion world: Her standout appearance at the Cannes Film Festival this year in the now iconic pink gown handmade by the content creator herself. Sporting her own designs, she turned heads not just on the red carpet but in the fashion industry as a whole. “The response was overwhelming,” she recalls, reflecting on the love she received for both her self-made outfits and her authenticity during interviews. Cannes wasn’t just another event for Nancy – it was the turning point that showcased her hard work and cemented her growing reputation.

Nancy is wearing a structured bodysuit, Mannatt Gupta; crystal hoop earrings, Isharya
